'''Leaf plastocron index''' is a measure of [[plant]] [[leaf]] age based on [[Morphology (biology)|morphological]] development (the [[plastochron]]). It is useful in studying plant development requiring destructive [[measurement]] on multiple individuals. By measuring a metric against morphological age, instead of [[chronological]] [[time]], one can reduce variations occurring between individuals, thus allowing greater focus on variations due to [[developmental biology|development]].<ref>Meicenheimer, R. D. (2014). The plastochron index: Still useful after nearly six decades. American Journal of Botany, 101(11), 1821-1835.</ref>

