{{Infobox journal | title = Science, Technology, & Human Values | cover = Science, Technology & Human Values.tif | editor = Edward J. Hackett | discipline = [[Science, technology and society]]; [[Sociology]] | former_names = | abbreviation = Sci. Technol. Hum. Values | publisher = [[SAGE Publications]] | country = | frequency = Bimonthly | history = 1967–present | openaccess = | license = | impact = 2.941 | impact-year = 2017 | website = http://www.uk.sagepub.com/journals/Journal200858/title | link1 = http://sth.sagepub.com/content/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://sth.sagepub.com/content/by/year | link2-name = Online archive | ISSN = 0162-2439 | eISSN = | OCLC = 51204698 | LCCN = 82642469 }} '''''Science, Technology, & Human Values''''' ('''''ST&HV''''') is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] that covers research on the relationship of [[science, technology and society|science and technology with society]]. The journal's [[editor-in-chief]] is Edward J. Hackett ([[Arizona State University]]). From the "Newsletters of the Program on the Public Conceptions of Science" that [[Gerald Holton]] established in 1972, it became ''The Newsletter on Science, Technology, & Human Values'', in 1976.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Shelanski|first=Vivien B.|date=October 1, 1976|title=Editor's Introduction|url=http://journals.sagepub.com/doi/10.1177/016224397600100401|journal=Science, Technology, & Human Values|volume=1|pages=1-2|doi=10.1177/016224397600100401|via=}}</ref> ''ST&HV'' is published by the [[Society for Social Studies of Science]], in conjunction with [[SAGE Publications]].
